Week Ending Aug 29, 2025
This report provides a summary of research produced by J.P. Morgan Global Bank Equity Research. Key highlights from the past week:
European Banks Daily: 22 August 2025
Polish Banks: Higher banking sector tax equal to \(5\%\) of NAV in 26E- 27E and to pressure COE
Azora Bank (8304): Want to focus on effects of partnership with Daiwa Securities Group
Large Cap Banks: Fed Weekly: Loans Flattish While Deposits Rose Modestly Last Week; C&I Related Loans, Deposits Up Modestly Midway Thru 2Q
Macquarie Group Limited: Laggard to catch up as rate cuts support medium- term earnings outlook; upgrade to OW
Bendigo and Adelaide Bank: FY25 result: Optimistic ROE target requires a lot of faith; more realistic path looks priced in
European Banks Daily: 26 August 2025
Communications Infrastructure: Impact of AT&T's Purchase of EchoStar Spectrum Licenses on Towers
Tyro Payments Limited: A churn of events - FY25 result
Philippine Banks: Buy the weakness; BDO back at 1x 2026E PB
Sinopac Financial Holdings: 1H25 results slightly ahead on better bank earnings
Chailease Holding: 1H25 results below on higher credit costs and slower portfolio growth
Vietnam Banks: Repositioning amidst the rally; u/g ACB to OW, d/g VPB to UW
French Banks: Navigating political risks
European Banks Daily: 27 August 2025
Brazilian Banks: July Data - Negative Agro Asset Quality and Private Payroll Reaccelerating
Futu Holdings: Assessing upside on multiple re- rating
European Banks Daily: 28 August 2025
Bank of Queensland: "Accelerating industry headwinds" at odds with recent peer results; retain UW
Korea Banks: BoK holds policy rate unchanged; limited downside risks to NIM amid improving macro

J.P. Morgan does and seeks to do business with companies covered in its research reports. As a result, investors should be aware that the firm may have a conflict of interest that could affect the objectivity of this report. Investors should consider this report as only a single factor in making their investment decision.

- Hua Nan FHC: 1H25 results slightly ahead on lower credit costs- XP: Model Update- Affirm: F4Q25 Recap: Record Notional Volume Growth; FY26 Guidance Ahead on Most Key Metrics- APRA Jul-25 Banking Stats: Business credit growth rebounds strongly in July; accelerating BOQ mortgage book run-off a concern- Metropolitan Bank: Model Update- Bank Central Asia (BCA): Model Update
All prices and valuations in this report are as of 28 Aug 2025 unless otherwise indicated.
